Program with the method name, “sum()” that accepts two
parameters from the user and print the sum of those two numbers. The
output format should be:
First number is:
Second number is:
Sum is:
import java.util.Scanner;     //importing scanner class from util package
public class acad {
	public static int sum(int a,int b) //Method 'sum' for adding two values in the parameter list
	{
		int d = a+b;
		return d;                        // returns the sum
	} 
	public static void main(String args[])  // main method from which sum method is called
	{
		
	Scanner sc =new Scanner(System.in);       // creating sc object for scanner class
	int a = sc.nextInt();                     // input for variable 'a' is taken from user using scanner class 
	int b =sc.nextInt();                      // input for variable  'b' is taken from user using scanner class
		                                         //Next three statements prints the text format given and answer along
	System.out.println( "First number is:"+a);
		System.out.println("Second number is:"+b);
		System.out.println("Sum is:"+sum(a,b));    // prints the return value from sum method
		
	}

}
